    "body": "> Change the current sub-linear issuance model to a linear issuance model (i.e., set adjusted_quotient = get_previous_total_balance(state) // BASE_REWARD_QUOTIENT). Since individual validator rewards no longer decrease with each new validator, there is no incentive to prevent new validators from joining.\r\n\r\nThe problem with this is that it imposes on the network too much uncertainty of two types: (i) uncertainty of total issuance, (ii) uncertainty of the level of security on the network. That is, if it turns out that whatever rate we set is not enough, almost no one will participate, whereas the inv-sqrt mechanism adds some natural self-correcting pressure against this.",
