    "body": "Upon further consideration, I think the gatekeeping attack should be considered from two facets: (1) rational validators excluding deposits and (2) rational validators excluding activations. Making deposit processing mandatory only solves (1). Rational validators will still exclude activation transactions from being included in the canonical beacon chain.\r\n\r\nThere are two ways I can think of preventing this. First is to also allow activations to be sent to a contract on the ETH1 chain, and making processing of these activation transactions mandatory. This of course is predicated on the perpetual existence of the PoW chain and the beacon chain's reliance on it. Second is to set base rewards to a constant rate, i.e., `B = k * Di`, which removes the incentive to perform a gatekeeping attack.\r\n\r\n[This paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/1811.00742) claims to provide a solution to this problem contained within a single PoS system, though I have not vetted it.\r\n\r\n",
